  "prompt": "Money laundering has to be illegal, right?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in most countries around the world. It is a financial crime that involves disguising the origins of money obtained through illegal activities (such as drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) to make it appear as if it comes from a legitimate source. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legal and usable\n\nIn the United States, money laundering is a federal crime with significant legal penalties, including hefty fines and potential imprisonment.",
